  "questions": [
    {
      "text": "In a child with thalassemia major, which of the following drugs should be started to reduce transfusion dependency?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Luspatercept"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Deferoxamine"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Deferiprone"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Deferasirox"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 0,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct answer is a: Luspatercept</strong></p>\n\n<p>The question is not on iron <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"11199cbd1816927771841f1eb35b86\">chelation</span> but measures to reduce <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"cbb73554631692777200444a9ea263\">transfusion</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4fe4b79dde16927771866f60a939e2\">dependency</span> or number of transfusions required per year.</p>\n\n<p>Luspatercept is a novel <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"892718f3e916927771871389d2e1a3\">erythroid</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"76948f718016927771924774ade7e9\">maturation</span> agent that promotes late-stage <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"317dbdacdb16927771878c7860f69b\">erythropoiesis</span> and improves <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"2a7f0b780c1692777187fe83ec76b1\">endogenous</span> HB production . It <strong>does not replace</strong> iron chelators that are used to prevent complications like <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"7976e13d711692777183e839c8a79c\">bronze diabetes</span> or cardiomyopathy.</p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p> </p>",
      "question_images": [],
      "explanation_video": null,
      "explanation_images": [],
      "explanation_audio_eng": null,
      "explanation_audio_hin": null
    },
    {
      "text": "A 4- year old child with anemia, chipmunk facies and splenomegaly is found to have low Hb A and elevated HbF and HbA2. He has received multiple blood transfusions for which no records are available Which of the following is least likely to occur as a complication in this case?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Lung fibrosis"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Cardiomyopathy"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Diabetes"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Infections with capsulated organisms"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 3,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct answer is d: Infections with capsulated organisms</strong></p>\n\n<p>Patients with <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"baed0c93841692777200be26c8b9d2\">thalassemia</span> major have <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"cbb73554631692777200444a9ea263\">transfusion</span> dependency. <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"cbb73554631692777200444a9ea263\">Transfusion</span> associated infections <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"8d0fca798b1692777191b6cd41880f\">linked</span> to <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"64bbd63a0c1692777190f0c8e06e91\">iron overload</span> are caused by <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b98ea6f7ff1692777202949d7a5b46\">yersinia</span> , <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"0df89fd47716927771914ac591d3a9\">listeria</span> and malaria.</p>\n\n<p>Excess iron can damage the lungs and heart causing <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"21e2d5a70616927772021fcdec0ca9\">fibrosis</span> and cardiomyopathy. Bronze diabetes can occur due to damage to <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"806eb8418c16927771822855b56695\">beta</span> cells.</p>\n\n<p>Infections with <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e26ba9a1d41692777187d0ad03a8c1\">encapsulated</span> organisms seen after splenectomy.</p>\n\n<p> </p>",
      "question_images": [],
      "explanation_video": null,
      "explanation_images": [],
      "explanation_audio_eng": null,
      "explanation_audio_hin": null
    },
    {
      "text": "Investigation of choice for diagnosis of beta thalassemia ?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "NESTROFT"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Gene sequencing"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "HPLC"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Hemoglobin electrophoresis"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 1,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct answer is b: Gene sequencing</strong></p>\n\n<p>WHO and Thalassemia International Federation guidelines now recommend molecular confirmation for all cases for diagnosis by demonstration of HBB gene mutation. Additional benefits are</p>\n\n<ol>\n\t<li>It allows accurate genetic counseling</li>\n\t<li>Guides <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d554413593169277719693b8e38638\">prenatal</span> testing via <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e1fbc0e52216927771842f23df5eae\">chorionic villus</span> sampling.</li>\n</ol>",
      "question_images": [],
      "explanation_video": null,
      "explanation_images": [],
      "explanation_audio_eng": null,
      "explanation_audio_hin": null
    },
    {
      "text": "Earliest radiological finding in patients with beta thalassemia is",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Widening of diploic spaces of skull"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Lytic lesion in vertebrae"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Squaring of metacarpals"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "AVN of metacarpals"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 2,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct answer is c: Squaring of metacarpals </strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>The earliest skeletal deformities in <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"baed0c93841692777200be26c8b9d2\">thalassemia</span> are observed in the metacarpals, metatarsals and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"27cd397275169277719513776c38c8\">phalanges</span> of hands. The patient develops <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"c8a8c935a41692777191610f6aacb4\">marrow</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4c5d5ef6c31692777189820d4b320d\">hyperplasia</span> causing <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"721937292f1692777185048f04ce29\">cortical</span> thinning and a “squared or sausage-shaped configuration” of these small <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"98d387b7bd1692777201278b27be72\">tubular</span> bones. Subsequently widening of diploic spaces with prominent bone trabeculations called “hair on end” appearance is seen.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><br />\n </p>",
      "question_images": [],
      "explanation_video": null,
      "explanation_images": [],
      "explanation_audio_eng": null,
      "explanation_audio_hin": null
    },
    {
      "text": "A 2 year old child is undergoing workup for severe anemia. Labs show Low MCV, Increased MCHC. USG abdomen shows enlarged spleen with acoustic shadows in gall bladder. Which of the following is not correct about this patient?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Peripheral smear shows RBC that lack central pallor"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Black pigmented gall stones in gall bladder"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Counsel about Elective splenectomy"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Defective gene on chromosome 14"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 3,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct answer is d: Defective gene on <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"7157c1f59916927771846116d74646\">chromosome</span> 14</strong></p>\n\n<p>The key word is increased MCHC with <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"53bee2a41216927771814d7ec3a67f\">anemia</span> suggesting diagnosis as <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"ee5175c06116927771880846d1cbe0\">hereditary</span> spherocytosis. The <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"54d290087e1692777180c6cc682930\">acoustic</span> shadows in the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"bec5d0b8cb1692777188267d64974a\">gall</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e6cfda323816927771839cc83e376d\">bladder</span> are <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"85dafbf32f1692777195b9d9f035d8\">pigmented</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"bec5d0b8cb1692777188267d64974a\">gall</span> stones. Spherocytes lack central <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"dd5d862f051692777194647422e1c9\">pallor</span> and are smaller in size than normal RBC.</p>\n\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:602px\">\n\t<tbody>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>GENE</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Chromosomal mutation</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Protein produced</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Pattern of Inheritance</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><em>SPTA1</em></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>1q22-q23</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>α-Spectrin</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p> </p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>HE (dominant)</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><em>SPTB</em></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>14q23-q24.1</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>β-Spectrin</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p> </p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>HE (dominant)</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><em>ANK1</em></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>8p11.2</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Ankyrin</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p> </p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>HS (dominant)</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><em>SLC4A1</em></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>17q21</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>B and 3; also known as <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"53e82fca731692777181e629a02799\">anion</span> exchanger</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>HS (dominant)</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>",
      "question_images": [],
      "explanation_video": null,
      "explanation_images": [],
      "explanation_audio_eng": null,
      "explanation_audio_hin": null
    },
    {
      "text": "In a transfusion dependent thalassemia major child, deferoxamine should be started at serum ferritin values > __________________ ug/L",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "500"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "1000"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "1500"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "2000"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 1,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct answer is b: 1000</strong></p>\n\n<p>Deferoxamine <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"11199cbd1816927771841f1eb35b86\">chelation</span> should begin in chronic transfusional iron overload-</p>\n\n<ol>\n\t<li>10-15 transfusions or Two years after starting transfusions</li>\n\t<li>Serum <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"91d0e4c6fa16927772025f96b44b27\">ferritin</span> > 1,000 µg/L</li>\n\t<li>Liver iron concentration > 3 mg Fe/g dry weight</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p>This information should not be mixed with indications for starting DFO in <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4cdc8161f71692777180df58cafa93\">acute</span> iron <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"072b8af16e1692777196f21b086f92\">poisoning</span> when <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"1ffaec13de169277719828374cfda0\">serum</span> iron > 500 ug/dl at 4-6 hours after ingestion.</p>",
      "question_images": [],
      "explanation_video": null,
      "explanation_images": [],
      "explanation_audio_eng": null,
      "explanation_audio_hin": null
    },
    {
      "text": "A 10 year old boy presents with pallor. Work up shows Hb= 8 gm%, P.smear has anisocytosis with poikilocytosis, Hemoglobin electrophoresis report has Hb A = 60%, HbF = 34%, HbA2 = 6%. Diagnosis is?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Thalassemia minor"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Thalassemia major"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Thalassemia intermedia"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Thalassemia trait"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 2,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct answer is c: Thalassemia intermedia</strong></p>\n\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:600px\">\n\t<tbody>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Condition </strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>HbA</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>HbF</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>HbA2 </strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Notes</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Thalassemia minor/trait</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Usually >90%</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>N or slightly increased</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Increased</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p>(3.5 - 8%)</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>HbF rarely >5%</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Thalassemia intermedia</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Markedly reduced</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>↑(up to 30 - 70%)</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Increased</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Variable <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"cbb73554631692777200444a9ea263\">transfusion</span> need</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Thalassemia major</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Absent or very low (<10%)</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Very High (70-90%)</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Normal/slightly Increased</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Transfusion - dependent from infancy</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p> </p>",
