      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 0,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct answer is A:. Extremely low oxygen affinity</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Hb Barts has extremely high oxygen affinity. That explains poor oxygen delivery to body tissue including heart leading to <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b0eb48bbf6169277718568c051e6ad\">congestive heart failure</span> and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"18b452e75916927771864c9ad533e1\">edema</span> ( <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"9996ef505516927771937fe4ef1222\">non</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b3c8b5ea2e169277718969e2c05fae\">immunogenic</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"7b09c2b34916927771896ff30fcaa0\">hydrops</span> fetalis). all hemoglobinopathies cause unstable structure of hemoglobin.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p> </p>",
      "question_images": [],
      "explanation_video": null,
      "explanation_images": [],
      "explanation_audio_eng": null,
      "explanation_audio_hin": null
    },
    {
      "text": "In a newly diagnosed beta thalassemia major patient which manifestation will not be seen?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Ectopic hematopoiesis"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Reticulocyte count of 0.1%"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Ineffective erythropoiesis"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Elevated LDH and low Haptoglobin levels"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 1,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct answer is b: <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"249592767b16927771976df58de24d\">Reticulocyte</span> count of 0.1%</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Normal <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"249592767b16927771976df58de24d\">reticulocyte</span> count is 0.5 -1.5% . <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d30ae941d516927771889351160b00\">hemolytic</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"53bee2a41216927771814d7ec3a67f\">anemia</span> will cause <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"249592767b16927771976df58de24d\">reticulocyte</span> count to increase. Patients develop <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"0ba1f7edfa1692777187ae6f51e603\">extramedullary</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"bb774c3cec1692777188327b4bc737\">hematopoiesis</span> also called <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"0decefe0901692777186f7f3f89b2a\">ectopic</span> hematopoiesis. It means RBC <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3fda45538a1692777199ec2a5478a5\">synthesis</span> in liver and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"6a4861c8d71692777199aeb1d55c85\">spleen</span> which causes them to enlarge. The production of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"144d78fe4816927771852de984c62f\">defective</span> RBC containing <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a9268f2e1d16927771814cfef69cf4\">alpha</span> tetramers in the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5b9831f3aa169277718395d7361df6\">bone marrow</span> due to absence of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"806eb8418c16927771822855b56695\">beta</span> chains is present.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p> </p>",
