    {
      "text": "You are counseling parents of a 3 year old severely anaemic child diagnosed with hereditary spherocytosis about surgical options. Which of the following will you inform them about?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Splenectomy"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Gall bladder removal"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Splenectomy plus gall bladder removal"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Nephrectomy"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 0,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct answer is a: Splenectomy</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Elective <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3c702f2ca816927771998e8ca552e1\">splenectomy</span> should be done in severe cases of HS by 4-6 years of age. For mild cases <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3c702f2ca816927771998e8ca552e1\">splenectomy</span> can be avoided. Gall <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e6cfda323816927771839cc83e376d\">bladder</span> removal is not done in all cases and must be done if symptoms are present. All cases should be vaccinated with Neisseria meningitidis and Haemophilus influenzae before splenectomy.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p> </p>",
